im working on code to identify month by month how many prayers I missed and am writing a flutter program to be able to easily set a percentage missed in a settings screen and in edit details you can drill down month by month to set the 5 daily prayers from fajir thuhur asr maghrib and isha percentages for that year and that month. I think we should set a datamodel that makes sense where each month has total missed total prayed total percentage missed and total percentage prayed derived and set each time something is changed. it should use Hive service as a db and should be really simple for web, android using material and ios using cupertino, The program should have homescreen showcasing the total prayed out of total possible as a progress bar on the top with a number showing the total on the right and the number for total prayed on the left and 5 buttons with percentage progress bars for each prayer so you can press then and increment that prayer's total. When pressed it should go to the "furthest back" oldest prayer missed, so for instance if you prayed 50% of 2024 it will go back to the end of June and start of july and start adding that prayer again, everything before that will have an indicator for that prayer in the database saying it's done when the button is pushed the top bar should indicate progress as well as that current buttons bar. 

update the flutter project below to use the logic we just described. Return first main.dart myApp.dart hive_service.dart and prayer_data.dart
think step by step about how to do this best return the files above, we will then make a plan to update prayer services and provider next

